        <bioghist>
            <p>Joseph Edward Burns was born in Honesdale, PA in 1879. Burns was widely known throughout the country and abroad as a manufacturer and inventor of many machines and devices relating to cutlery and the cut glass industry. He started out as a manufacturer of cut glass and an instructor in glass cutting. For a time he had factories in England and Canada, and he traveled throughout Europe. In 1919, Burns patented a serrated knife which was the first of its kind and the foundation of his business, the Burns Manufacturing Company. The Burns Manufacturing Company was located alongside the Erie Canal on Water Street in Syracuse, NY. In 1914, the company established a glass cutting factory in Canastota, NY. Burns was also affiliated with the Norton Company in Worcester, MA.</p>
        <p>Mr. Burns died on April 15, 1942 at his home in Syracuse, NY.</p>
        </bioghist>
